SIMON SAYS GAME

Welcome to the Simon Says game! This project is a digital implementation of the classic Simon Says electronic game, developed using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

How to Play
1. Game Rules: The game follows the original rules of Simon Says. A white flash indicates the game's signal, and a black flash occurs when the user clicks the button.
2. Game Sequence: The sequence of button flashes is stored in an array and displayed in the console on the right side of the game screen.
3. Game Over: If the user enters the wrong sequence, the game ends, and the final score is displayed.

How to Run
To play the game, simply hit any key on your keyboard and continue the game by mouse clicks.
once game ended the process can be repeated.
